      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2257: SwarmLoaded is emitted before loadMissingBodyOverwrites() runs, so the initial payload delivered to clients still contains untranslated/unmodified bodies. This contradicts the new ChatHandler contract that transformations happen before SwarmLoaded and causes clients to receive stale data followed by separate update signals. Move the overwrite loading/transformation before emitting SwarmLoaded, or apply the transformed pluginData to the messages vector before emission.\n```suggestion\n#ifdef ENABLE_PLUGIN\nif (auto convPtr \u003d convWeak.lock())\n    convPtr-\u003eloadMissingBodyOverwrites();\n#endif\nemitSignal\u003clibjami::ConversationSignal::SwarmLoaded\u003e(id, accountId, conversationId, messages);\n```",
